Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking. Once cooked, remove from the oven and leave to the side.

Quarter the @pear{1} and remove the core. Cut lengthways into 1cm wide slices. Break up the @feta cheese{100%g} into small chunks. Set both aside. Put the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @honey{15%ml} into a #large bowl{} and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Add a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{} and mix together with a #fork. Leave to the side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, add the pear slices and cook until they have softened, and slightly browned, turning them a couple of times, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, gently transfer to the #bowl{} with your dressing. Leave to the side.

Pop the now empty pan back on medium-high heat, add a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry. Season the @British chicken thighs{4} with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Once hot, lay in the chicken skin-side down and fry until the skin is golden and crisp, ~{5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once golden, turn and cook for ~{5%minutes} on the other side, then continue cooking, turning every ~{2%minutes} for ~{4-6%minutes} more mins or until the chicken is cooked through.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove it to a #board{} and leave to rest for a couple of mins. While the chicken rests, put the potatoes into the bowl with the pear and dressing. Add in half the feta and all of the @wild rocket{40%g}. Toss everything together (or use your hands) to gently combine.

Thinly slice the chicken. Divide the salad between #bowls{} and top with the sliced chicken and the remaining feta. Enjoy!